\end{array}
\right)$

Plugging in the values of $\vec{a}$ and $\vec{b}$, we get:

$\vec{a} \times \vec{b} = \left(
\begin{array}{c}
-\frac{9}{10} \cdot \frac{24}{5} - \frac{23}{5} \cdot \frac{26}{5} \\
\frac{23}{5} \cdot \frac{77}{10} - \left(-\frac{47}{10}\right) \cdot \frac{24}{5} \\
\left(-\frac{47}{10}\right) \cdot \frac{26}{5} - \left(-\frac{9}{10}\right) \cdot \frac{77}{10} \\
\end{array}
\right)$

Simplifying each component, we get:

$\vec{a} \times \vec{b} = \left(
\begin{array}{c}
-\frac{1632}{25} \\
\frac{2671}{50} \\
-\frac{1043}{50} \\
\end{array}
\right)$

Therefore, the cross product of $\vec{a}$ and $\vec{b}$ is $\left(
\begin{array}{c}
-\frac{1632}{25} \\
\frac{2671}{50} \\
-\frac{1043}{50} \\
\end{array}
\right)$.
####
The answer is $\vec{a} \times \vec{b} = \left(
\begin{array}{c}
-\frac{1632}{25} \\
\frac{2671}{50} \\
-\frac{1043}{50} \\
\end{array}
\right)$

